  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "We find that, in most cases, models demonstrate lower label bias on tasks with semantically equivalent labels.",
    "This is especially evident in settings with few or no demonstrations, where models are typically strongly biased (§4.1).",
    "Still, RSD levels for such tasks remain relatively high across all evaluated settings.",
    "Further, we observe that instruction-tuned models prompted with 8 or more demonstrations are often more biased on this subset of tasks.",
    "In summary, although using semantically equivalent labels may potentially mitigate bias in scenarios with limited demonstrations, LLMs still exhibit substantial label bias when faced with such labels."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}